The paper discusses a challenge related to deep neural networks (DNNs) and sparse data, which are both topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The challenge also involves computations that can be implemented using the GraphBLAS.org standard, which is related to graph algorithms and data structures, making the distributed, parallel, and high-performance computing (cs.DC) sub-category a likely fit as well. Additionally, the challenge involves image data from the MNIST dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) research. Finally, the paper mentions prior challenges from the field of visual analytics, which could also place it in the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), although this is less likely given the focus on DNNs and sparse data.
